goals.question: What is the correlation between fertility rate and life expectancy?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of fertility rate vs life expectancy
goals.rationale: This visualization can help us understand if there is a relationship between fertility rate and life expectancy. If there is a negative correlation, it could indicate that countries with higher fertility rates have lower life expectancies and vice versa.

goals.question: What is the distribution of fertility rates across countries?
goals.rationale: This visualization can help us understand the range of fertility rates across countries and identify any outliers or patterns in the data.

goals.question: How have fertility rates changed over time?
goals.visualization: line chart of fertility rates over time
goals.rationale: This visualization can help us identify any trends or patterns in fertility rates over time and understand if there have been any significant changes in recent years.

goals.question: What is the distribution of life expectancies across countries?
goals.rationale: This visualization can help us understand the range of life expectancies across countries and identify any outliers or patterns in the data.

goals.question: How do projected fertility rates compare to previous fertility rates?
goals.visualization: bar chart of previous fertility rates vs projected fertility rates
goals.rationale: This visualization can help us understand if there are any significant changes in fertility rates projected for the future compared to previous rates. It can also help us identify any countries where fertility rates are expected to change significantly.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['fertility'], data['life_expect'])
    plt.xlabel('Fertility Rate')
    plt.ylabel('Life Expectancy')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title('What is the correlation between fertility rate and life expectancy?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['fertility'])
    plt.xlabel('Fertility Rate')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    ax = plt.gca()
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of fertility rates across countries?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    data = data.groupby('year')['fertility'].mean().reset_index()
    
    plt.plot(data['year'], data['fertility'])
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title("How have fertility rates changed over time?")
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data.plot.bar(x='country', y=['p_fertility', 'n_fertility'])
    plt.title("How do projected fertility rates compare to previous fertility rates?")
    plt.xlabel("Country")
    plt.ylabel("Fertility Rate")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
